Northern Lights Lake in Nolalu, Ontario. Best walleye lake I've ever fished. This will be my eleventh year going up. Trophy walleye. Trophy lakers and pike too. 5 pound smallies all day long. My father landed a 31" wally a few years back.

All mine are in eastern Canada due to demographics. I would like to get out to LOW someday. Did fish Minnetonka once on a training trip to Minneapolis. Calabogie (my first) Gananoque Whitefish Clear Bob's Ontario Loughborough Newboro Wolfe Canoe Lady Evelyn Gogama Pebonshewie Ramsey (a zillion pike) Cabonga Hebert Several hike in or flyins, the names escape me. And then there's the rivers, but I won't go there. They were all great
